.TH VAULT 1 "February 2026" "password-vault 0.1.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
vault \- local password vault and TOTP generator

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vault
[\fIcommand\fR] [\fIoptions\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B vault
is a local command-line password vault designed for use on Termux and Linux.
It provides secure storage primitives and a TOTP (RFC 6238) authenticator.

This tool is intended for local use and learning purposes.

.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B totp \fISECRET\fR
Generate a 6-digit Time-based One-Time Password (TOTP) from a Base32 secret.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -h, --help
Show help message and exit.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Generate a TOTP code:
.RS
vault totp JBSWY3DPEHPK3PXP
.RE

.SH SECURITY
Never pass real secrets directly on the command line.
Command-line arguments may be visible via shell history or process listings.

.SH FILES
.TP
~/.config/password-vault/
Default configuration directory (future use).

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
Success.
.TP
1
General error.

